text:
Chicken Chop Lor Mee $4.50 (4/10)
Gravy is thick, and very starchy, with a slight herbal sweetness. I had to add a generous amount of vinegar to thin it out, which altered the flavour profile.

The chicken chop batter had the taste of flour, which could have been improved by longer seasoning.  Lastly the hard boiled egg was overcooked, and had the sulphuric smell. This was edible, but never again.

Had the 5$ lor mee. Gravy was thick but lacks a bit of flavour. Ingredients were generous. You can add more vinegar, chilli or garlic at the self-serve.

Overall recommend if you are nearby.

Good enough noodle.
Ingredients is ok for the price.
Condiments can self add, so it still generous
